code: @Override protected MultiPoint createTestInstance() {     int size = randomIntBetween(1, 10).     List<Point> arr = new ArrayList<>().     for (int i = 0. i < size. i++) {         arr.add(randomPoint()).     }     return new MultiPoint(arr). }

public void testBasicSerialization() throws IOException, ParseException {     assertEquals("multipoint (2.0 1.0)", WellKnownText.toWKT(new MultiPoint(Collections.singletonList(new Point(1, 2))))).     assertEquals(new MultiPoint(Collections.singletonList(new Point(1, 2))), WellKnownText.fromWKT("multipoint (2 1)")).     assertEquals("multipoint EMPTY", WellKnownText.toWKT(MultiPoint.EMPTY)).     assertEquals(MultiPoint.EMPTY, WellKnownText.fromWKT("multipoint EMPTY)")). }
